INSERT INTO `employer` VALUES(949, 'SHIVAN & NARRESH', 951, 1, '\r\n‘SHIVAN & NARRESH’ was launched in Cannes at ‘Mare di Moda’ with their 100% stitch free line called Insectoid. SHIVAN & \r\nNARRESH has a unique signature style that is bold, confident &  sophisticated. Flawless lines, undisputed eye for detail and utter \r\nsophistication are words that could be used to define the brand.\r\nCurrently based out of New Delhi, SHIVAN Bhatiya mastered the art of leather corsetry and accessories for four years from \r\nNational Institute of Fashion Technology, New Delhi, learning the functions and craftsmanship of leather in women’s wear lingerie. \r\nWhile NARRESH Kukreja specialized in women’s wear for four years in Fashion & Textiles. Subsequent to their graduation, they \r\nwere awarded scholarships to complete their Masters in Milan & Rome at the Istituto Europeo di Design. After the launch in \r\nCannes, the duo shifted their studio to India, and became the first mainstream beachwear designers doing 100% handcrafted stitchfree beachwear along with ready to wear swimwear made all in 100% Italian fabrics and complementing resortwear.\r\nSHIVAN & NARRESH is also the first Indian brand to showcase at the Mercedes Benz Fashion Week Swim 2012 at Miami and also \r\nto participate in the Swimwear Association of Florida’s SwimShow 2012.\r\nSHIVAN & NARRESH are recipients of several awards in recognition of their design & creativity. They received the SWAROVSKI \r\nMost Creative Designer of the Year (‘07); Debutant Designer of the Year (‘07) at India Fashion Week and winners of the World of \r\nWearable Art Awards, Wellington, New Zealand(‘06).The duo were discovered in 2006 by MITTELMODA, the oldest Italian talent \r\nsearch organization, based in Gorizia, Italy through Mittelmoda International Beachwear Awards in Bali.They were also part of Elle \r\nMagazine’s power list for 2010 and are the Brand Ambassadors of Cotton Council International (CCI) 2009/10. They are also the \r\nrecepients of Best Emerging Designers 2010 at the Marie Claire Fashion Awards 2010, Best Resortwear at the Elle Style Awards \r\n2010 and the 2nd Runners Up at the Swarovski Jewellery Design Awards 2010.  Recently, they have received the Today’s Youth Asia’s \r\nYoung Achievers Award in collaboration with the Indian Embassy at Kathmandu.\r\nApart from selling from select stores, resorts & hotels, the brand is one of the only brands in the world to offer made-to-measure', 'shivanandnarresh@gmail.com', 1, '93', '', '', 1, 'Vivek', '9999692539', 'dbadmin', '2012-09-16 14:56:10', '0', 'Bandra', '');
